    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "The Prophet (SAWW) identifies two of the worst human failings: being too heedless to supplicate to God, and being too stingy to greet others with salam. This hadith, narrated through Abu Hurayra in a Sunni-Shia shared chain, was delivered as part of the Prophet's general moral counsel to his community. The original audience understood supplication (du'a) as a fundamental act of worship showing dependence on God, and salam as the basic social bond between believers, making neglect of either a mark of spiritual and social deficiency.",
        "key_terms": {
          "الدعاء": "Du'a (supplication), the act of calling upon God in prayer",
          "السلام": "Salam (peace greeting), the Islamic greeting of peace"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did the Prophet say about supplication and greeting others with salam?"
      },
